The paper proposes a method for solving few shot learning problems by augmenting neural nets with symbolic learning. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to visual discrimination puzzles, which involves recognizing objects and object relationships, and learning higher-level concepts from very few images. This suggests that the paper may also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses logic constraint solvers, which suggests that it may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
